&lt;p&gt;Robyn Stratton-Berkessel includes a list of exercises to do at Appreciative Inquiry Workshops. In her Compassionate Connections worksheet, she encourages us to ask the following questions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Remember a time when you experienced a deep connection with others and a sense of compassion filled you&amp;mdash;you reacted in a way that strengthened your sense of being in community with others.&amp;rdquo;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;Describe the situation. What happened?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;How were you involved&amp;mdash;as a participant or as an observer?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;What about that experience filled you with a sense of compassionate connection to others?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;ldquo;What did you notice at the time about the behavior of others involved?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;What did you notice about yourself in this story of compassionate connection?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;hr /&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&amp;ldquo;What did you notice about your feelings? Where did you feel those feelings in your body?&lt;/p&gt;

